{"word":"γοάω","slug":"γοάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γοάω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γόος'><el>γόος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to wail, groan, weep</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to bewail, mourn, lament, weep for</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>ὑπέρ τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Moschus'>Mosch.</a></b>:—so also in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>γοᾶται</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/>"}]}